 HN23[
] Section 1 of the Sherman Act broadly prohibits "[e]very contract, combination . . ., or conspiracy, in restraint of trade or commerce among the several States." 15 U.S.C. § 1. The term "restraint of trade" has been limited to "undue" (unreasonable) 
restrains. Amex, 138 S.Ct. at 2283.

